What is Data Cleaning?

Data cleaning means fixing problems in the dataset before using it for Machine Learning.

Real-world data is rarely perfect. It usually has problems like:

Missing values

Duplicate records

Inconsistent column formats

Wrong data types

If we don’t fix these issues, the ML model may learn wrong patterns.

Common Data Cleaning Tasks
1️⃣ Handle Missing Values

NaN means missing data.

Ways to handle missing values

• Remove rows with missing values
• Fill with average value
• Fill with median or mode
import pandas as pd

# Load dataset
df = pd.read_csv("dataset.csv")

# Check missing values
print(df.isnull().sum())

# Fill missing values with column mean
df.fillna(df.mean(numeric_only=True), inplace=True)

2️⃣ Remove Duplicates
# Check duplicate rows
print(df.duplicated().sum())

# Remove duplicates
df.drop_duplicates(inplace=True)

3️⃣ Standardize Column Names

Sometimes column names are messy.
# Convert column names to lowercase
df.columns = df.columns.str.lower()

# Replace spaces with underscore
df.columns = df.columns.str.replace(" ", "_")

print(df.columns)

